===United Kingdom===
In 2010, a campaign by the [[Home Office]] featured adverts targeting "boys and girls aged 13 to 18" via television, radio, Internet, and poster campaigns.  The campaign followed research by the [[NSPCC]] indicating that approximately one-quarter of 13- to 17-year-old females had experienced physical abuse from a dating partner.<ref>{{cite news | last = Staff writer | title = Teenage domestic violence tackled by advert campaign | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/8515601.stm | website = news.bbc.co.uk | publisher = [[BBC news]] | location = London | date = 15 February 2010 | accessdate = 19 November 2014 }}</ref>
